To make a more quantitative estimate, we considered all available midshelf (50 m # z bot # 100 m) CTD profiles collected within the latitude band 428-488N during July-September of multiple years . Data were taken from the RISE and ECOHAB-PNW cruises, the 2013 version of the World Ocean Database, and other recent and historical CTD collections. In total, only 588 profiles satisfied the above restrictions. Following Lentz (2008) , each profile was interpolated to a 5-m vertical grid, and linear trends were fit to the data at each depth level. The resulting summertime-mean, depth-averaged (from 75-m depth to the surface), alongshelf density gradient was r y 5 21.0 3 10 26 (kg m
